</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64250768"><p>Well, TFS gives the numbers behind the claim - Q3 2023 down on Q2, and  Q4 down even further, by 10.2%. The overall 2023 numbers don't invalidate the quarterly trend. However with the surge in consumer debt, credit card delinquencies etc through 2023, it seems more likely to me that people are not buying EVs for financial reasons, rather than any change in sentiment about EVs. The jury's still out over hard landing/soft landing etc, but there's no doubt that consumers have been under increasing financial constraints in the last year, and that seems likely to have an effect on their purchasing choices.</p></div>
	</div>

