			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64250720">		
		on Monday February 19, 2024 @04:00AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23231052&amp;cid=64250720">#64250720</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64250720">Here is the key phrase, buried under a bunch of innuendo: "EV sales growth also has slowed..."  Sales <i>growth</i>.  See the moving goalpost?  Quarterly dings aside, all they're talking about is slower than expected sales <i>growth</i>.  In other words, they're spinning a slower <i>acceleration</i> as if it were an actual decline, and deliberately picking their reference frame to see it that way.
<br>
<br>
Year-on-year is just fine, but if they do quarterly, they can spin it this way.  But if it were the other way around, they would have picked the other frame in order to have the same clickbait framing.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64250720">
