</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64251878"><p>At 32 cents per kWh it costs under $20 to charge a 60 kWh EV. That cost goes down further if a residence has solar or charges during off peak hours.</p><p>I remember filling my car for $20 back when I was a teenager. I don't think gas is that cheap even in Alaska. Maybe it's still that cheap in Saudi Arabi.</p></div>
	</div>

