Top tip for journalists: If you're going to ask your readers a rhetorical question, you better have answers for them, or at least know what you're writing about. Your job is to leave readers well-informed &amp; with a reasonable understanding after they've read your piece. They're not going to remember a list of mostly unrelated stats that you found on Google. Or maybe you just don't care as long as the clicks &amp; the pay checks keep coming in?</div>
